(21, 'ACT011', 'Paragliding', 'air', '2;', '661942889f512_Pasted image 34.png;66194288a33fc_Pasted image 35.png;66194288a90f1_Pasted image 36.png;', '<p>Paragliding is a recreational adventure sport in which the pilot floats beneath a wide canopy of light, free-flying, parachute-like material on legs linked to his or her body. Paraglider pilots may stay aloft for up to 3 hours, ascend to 15,000 feet, and travel hundreds of kilometers thanks to thermal wind currents. David Barish pioneered paragliding in the mid-1960s, and it has since become the most accessible type of human flight.</p>', 'paragliding-bali', 'en', '2024-04-12 14:17:54', '2024-04-12 14:17:54'),
