(27, 'DST014', 'Goa Gajah Temple', 'ubud', '6619f147bd3e7_Pasted image 54.png;6619f147c1a52_Pasted image 55.png;', '<p>Tourists, both international and Indonesian, visit this tourist attraction almost every day. Because tourists are really interested in this tourist attraction. This tourist destination is included in the tour schedules of several low-cost Bali travel package service providers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The man-made cave, which has become a historical landmark in Bali, is the main draw of Goa Gajah.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Goa Gajah has a distinct personality. The traditional Buddhist and Hindu place of worship is an open area with a temple or shrine rising to the top. In contrast, Goa Gajah is a devotional site that protrudes inward in the shape of a cave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Within Goa Gajah, there are several places to meditate. Goa Gajah is an Indian town.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>History</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The word Goa Gajah comes from the word &ldquo;Lwa Gajah&rdquo;. In the Negarakertagama ejection composed by Mpu Prapanca in 1365 AD, there is the name &ldquo;Lwa Gajah&rdquo;. If interpreted, into Indonesian, then the word &ldquo;Lwa&rdquo; means river and Elephant means a temple where Buddhist monks worship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So the name &ldquo;Lwa Gajah&rdquo; can be interpreted as a hermitage of Buddhist monks whose location is on the bank of a river.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The uniqueness of Goa Gajah</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Goa Gajah tourist attraction is loved by tourists because it offers a lot of uniqueness. Then what are the uniqueness contained in this tourist attraction?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The entrance through the mouth of the cave is only enough for 1 person.<br />\r\nOutside the entrance there is a carving and 2 guardian statues.<br />\r\nThe inside of the cave is shaped like the letter T, about 2 meters high and 2 meters wide.<br />\r\nOn the left and right of the aisle there are also alcoves which may have been a hermitage in ancient times. But now tourists can sit or lie there.<br />\r\nAt the west end of the hall there is a statue of Ganesha and at the east end of the hall there are 3 phallus.<br />\r\nApart from that, around the cave area, there is also a petirtaan statue with seven statues of widyadara-widyadari holding holy water. There are seven statues in total, which are symbols of the seven rivers in India, the birthplace of Hinduism and Buddhism.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Location</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Goa Gajah Ubud is located west of Bedulu Village, Blahbatuh District, Gianyar Regency. The exact location is on the edge of a ravine and is the confluence of a small river in the village. If you depart from the city of Denpasar, the distance is about 26 km from the city of Denpasar with an estimated travel time of 1 hour.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Goa Gajah Entrance Ticket Prices</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Every tourist who has a vacation to the tourist attractions of Goa Gajah Gianyar is required to pay an entrance ticket. Then how much is the entrance fee for the Goa Gajah Gianyar Bali tourist attraction? The following is a table of entrance ticket prices for the Goa Gajah Bali tourist attraction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ticket Price Category</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Entrance ticket IDR 50,000 / person</li>\r\n	<li>Car Parking IDR 5,000 / car</li>\r\n	<li>Motorcycle Parking IDR 2,000 / motorcycle</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'goa-gajah-tremple', 'en', '2024-04-13 02:43:25', '2024-04-13 02:43:25'),
